<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id602cc25f-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58" identifier="/us/usc/t30/s1013"><num value="1013">§ 1013.</num><heading> Surface land use</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Subject to the other provisions of this chapter, a lessee shall be entitled to use so much of the surface of the land covered by his geothermal lease as may be found by the Secretary to be necessary for the production, utilization, and conservation of geothermal resources.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id602cc260-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58">(<ref href="/us/pl/91/581/s14">Pub. L. 91–581, § 14</ref>, <date date="1970-12-24">Dec. 24, 1970</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/84/1571">84 Stat. 1571</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/109/58/tII/s236/14">Pub. L. 109–58, title II, § 236(14)</ref>, <date date="2005-08-08">Aug. 8, 2005</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/119/672">119 Stat. 672</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
